To produce a SPARQL query for KG2 (OpenAlex) given the information about Christian A. Mueller from KG1 (DBLP), we need to map the relations between the two knowledge graphs and construct a query based on the provided ER2 mapping.

The ER2 mapping is as follows:

[
  {
    "DBLP": "https://dblp.org/pid/117/3215",
    "OpenAlex": [
      "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1895-987X"
    ]
  },
  {
    "DBLP": "<https://dblp.org/rdf/schema#authoredBy>",
    "OpenAlex": [
      "https://semopenalex.org/ontology/hasAuthorship",
      "https://semopenalex.org/ontology/hasAuthor"
    ]
  },
  {
    "DBLP": "<https://dblp.org/rdf/schema#yearOfPublication>",
    "OpenAlex": [
      "http://purl.org/spar/fabio/hasPublicationYear"
    ]
  }
]

From this, we can see that the relation `<https://dblp.org/rdf/schema#authoredBy>` in DBLP corresponds to the relation `https://semopenalex.org/ontology/hasAuthorship` or `https://semopenalex.org/ontology/hasAuthor` in OpenAlex, and `<https://dblp.org/rdf/schema#yearOfPublication>` in DBLP corresponds to the relation `http://purl.org/spar/fabio/hasPublicationYear` in OpenAlex.

Given the DBLP query `SELECT DISTINCT ?firstanswer ?secondanswer WHERE { ?firstanswer <https://dblp.org/rdf/schema#authoredBy> <https://dblp.org/pid/117/3215> . ?firstanswer <https://dblp.org/rdf/schema#yearOfPublication> ?secondanswer }`, we can construct the corresponding OpenAlex query as follows:

 PREFIX oa: <https://semopenalex.org/ontology/>

 SELECT DISTINCT ?work ?year
 WHERE {
   ?work oa:hasAuthorship ?authorship .
   ?authorship oa:hasAuthor ?author .
   ?author <https://dbpedia.org/ontology/orcidId> "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1895-987X" .
   ?work fabio:hasPublicationYear ?year .
 }

Here, we're selecting distinct publications (`?work`) and their publication years (`?year`) for the authors identified by the ORCID ID "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1895-987X".

However, the actual query we're looking for is to find the papers published by Christian A. Mueller, so we should use the correct ORCID ID for him instead of a placeholder.

The final, complete SPARQL query for KG2 (OpenAlex) is:

<sparql>
PREFIX oa: <https://semopenalex.org/ontology/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?work ?year
WHERE {
  ?work oa:hasAuthorship ?authorship .
  ?authorship oa:hasAuthor ?author .
  ?author <https://dbpedia.org/ontology/orcidId> "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1895-987X" .
  ?work fabio:hasPublicationYear ?year .
}
</sparql>

